Ad Text:
Digital Services
Joondalup Campus with Work from Home options
$136,958 to $143,228 PA (HEW 9) PRO-RATA 
Ongoing, Permanent Role 


Edith Cowan University

Are you ready to belong to a dynamic community where courage, creativity, and optimism are essential elements of our DNA? At ECU we’re inspired by the incredible achievements of Edith Cowan, the first woman elected to an Australian parliament and a lifelong champion of education. Empowered by her legacy, we’re united in our vision to lead the sector in educational experience and expand our impact through world-class research. 

Embrace an opportunity to become part of something extraordinary.

Digital Services at Edith Cowan University is responsible for delivering and evolving the digital platforms, data, and capabilities that enable teaching, research, and university operations. The team drives the strategy and roadmap for enterprise digital solutions, including core systems, analytics, data governance, integration, and emerging technologies such as AI.


Working in close partnership with business areas across the University, Digital Services focuses on building secure, reliable, and scalable platforms that improve staff productivity, enable data-driven decision-making, and support innovation. The service centre brings together architecture, delivery, and operational expertise to ensure digital solutions are aligned to enterprise standards while remaining practical, modern, and fit for purpose.

About the Opportunity

You will join a team of skilled digital and data professionals within Digital Services – Data Governance and Analytics, working collaboratively to deliver trusted, enterprise-wide data capabilities for the University.

Own and evolve the University’s enterprise data and integration architecture, aligning business concepts, data, systems, and digital platforms.
Define and govern canonical data models, standards, and integration patterns to enable consistent, reliable, and reusable data exchange.
Provide data and integration architecture assurance across digital initiatives, embedding data quality, privacy, and security by design.
Partner with delivery teams and vendors to translate requirements into scalable, secure integration designs and uplift organisational capability.

About you

To be successful in this role, you will demonstrate:

Proven experience leading enterprise data and integration architecture in complex environments, including data models, standards, and architectural patterns.
Strong knowledge of modern data and integration architectures and cloud platforms, with the ability to design secure, scalable, resilient, and cost-effective solutions.
Demonstrated experience embedding data quality, privacy, and security by design, aligned to governance and regulatory requirements.
Experience providing architectural assurance and design oversight across digital initiatives to ensure consistency, reuse, and sustainability.
Ability to collaborate effectively with technical and business stakeholders, delivery teams, and vendors in a federated delivery model.
Experience working within data governance frameworks, with an understanding of data lineage, stewardship, and the ethical use of data and AI.

Benefits of working at ECU

At ECU we’re committed to fostering a positive employment experience and believe this is fundamental to the success and satisfaction of our employees. Growth and development matter here, because we recognise people are at the centre of everything we do. Our thriving work culture is guided by the ECU values and complemented by a range of employee benefits; visit our website to read about flexible working arrangements, generous leave entitlements, our commitment to Wellbeing, exclusive corporate discounts and industry-leading superannuation.

Contact

Please contact Harpreet Khalsa on +61 86304 2832 or h.khalsa@ecu.edu.au for more information.

Application Process

Please upload an up-to-date resume (not more than 3 pages) your experience and achievements, along with a brief covering letter of no more than 2 pages outlining your suitability for the role.

Advert Closure

Applications close Sunday 15 February 2026 at 11:30pm AWST.

ECU reserves the right to close the advertisement before the stated closing date, and encourage applicants to submit their applications early.

PLEASE NOTE: APPLICATIONS WILL ONLY BE ACCEPTED FROM CANDIDATES WHO HAVE THE RELEVANT WORKING RIGHTS TO FILL THIS POSITION.

ECU is a diverse and inclusive workplace with specific strategies and initiatives in place to address underrepresentation of specific groups. We strongly encourage applications from the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander community.

We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability, age and faith. For more information on our commitment to equity and diversity, please visit our Inclusive Workplace website.

At ECU, we are committed to supporting adjustments throughout the recruitment and selection process, as well as during employment. We actively encourage people with disability to apply to ECU. To discuss how we can support adjustment requirements, please contact the person listed above.

The Senior Solution Architect is an important technical leader within our Digital Technology practice. This leader is responsible for developing, and overseeing the implementation of enterprise-scale digital solutions for clients across diverse industries. These industries include manufacturing, life sciences, consumer packaged goods, and industrial high-tech. You will be the bridge between complex technical systems and strategic our goals, ensuring that architectural decisions promote measurable value while upholding technical expertise.




You are passionate about the exciting world of digital technologies. This world includes the Internet of Things (IoT), Big Data, Advanced Analytics, Artificial Intelligence, and Machine Learning. You also has experience leading technical strategy and delivery for advisory and implementation projects.




Your Responsibilities:




Technical Strategy and Solution Architecture

Lead the design and implementation of scalable, and secure architectures that integrate multiple systems, platforms, and new technologies, with a focus on Industrial IoT and digital thread solutions.

Develop comprehensive technical strategies for cloud-native applications, enterprise technology platforms and data analytics pipelines.

Ensure seamless integration between software, hardware components, network infrastructure, and data flow across complex digital ecosystems, from the edge to the cloud.




Client Engagement and Advisory

Be a trusted technical advisor to clients, expressing complex architectural concepts to both technical and non-technical executive audiences.

Lead technical discovery sessions and workshop activities to understand client goals, define our requirements, and conceptualise solutions.

Work with our commercial team to develop and present solutions, demonstrations, and statements of work, including work plans, estimates, and project approaches.




Project Leadership and Delivery Excellence

Oversee the technical delivery of projects throughout their lifecycle, ensuring you exceed client expectations.

Provide technical leadership and mentorship to cross-functional teams, including developers, technical consultants, and business analysts, guiding them to follow established design principles and best practices.

Establish and manage technical governance, conduct architecture reviews, and incorporate DevOps and Agile methodologies to ensure delivery.




Capability and Practice Development

Contribute to the growth of our technical capabilities by assisting with the recruitment, hiring, and mentoring of junior technical resources.

Promote the development and documentation of technical standards, reusable architectural patterns, and best practices for the Enterprise Technology practice.

Stay at the forefront of new technologies, recommending solutions that value to our clients.




The Essentials - You Will Have:

We require a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, or a related technical field. We also prefer a Master's degree.

Technical Competencies: IoT & Industrial Domain: Deep expertise in modern technology stacks. This includes experience with data modeling, services development, and connectivity using Edge SDKs or industrial protocols (e.g., OPC, MQTT, Modbus). Experience with manufacturing operations and typical OT/IT landscapes (e.g., MES, SCADA, PLC, ERP, Asset Management).

Cloud Architecture: Proficiency in designing and deploying solutions on one or more major cloud platforms (AWS, Microsoft Azure, GCP), including cloud-native and hybrid architectures.

Data & Analytics: Experience with advanced analytics and machine learning disciplines (model development, deployment) and integration with 'Big Data' platforms. Competency in RDBMS (e.g., MS SQL Server, Oracle) and NoSQL databases.

Integration: Strong knowledge of modern integration standards such as RESTful APIs, OData, and message-oriented middleware (MQ).

Software Engineering: Competency in object-oriented development (Java or .NET), modern web development (e.g., Angular, React), and Agile/SDLC software development practices.




The Preferred - You Might Also Have:




Consulting & Leadership Skills

Client Leadership: Exceptional client-facing Experience establishing communication and engagement with prospects, experience digging into prospects' pain points and validating the issues they're facing and act as a trusted advisor.

Team Collaboration: Mentor remote and globally distributed development teams, ensuring partner support and collaborative success.

Business Acumen: Ability to understand our requirements and translate them into well-engineered, value-driven technical solutions.




Work Environment

You will operate in a team that values innovation, collaboration, and learning.

The position is remote-friendly, but requires the ability to travel to client sites for workshops, presentations, and project milestones (travel requirements can vary).




What We Offer:

Our benefits package includes …

Comprehensive mindfulness programs with a premium membership to Calm

Volunteer Paid Time off available after 6 months of employment for eligible employees

Company volunteer and donation matching program – Your volunteer hours or personal cash donations to an eligible charity can be matched with a charitable donation.

Employee Assistance Program

Personalized wellbeing programs through our OnTrack program

On-demand digital course library for professional development

... and other local benefits!

At Rockwell Automation we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive and authentic workplace, so if you're excited about this role but your experience doesn't align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right person for this or other roles.

Job Title: Technical Services Engineer / CAMO - 12 Month Contract
Ad Text:
12-month contract position. This opportunity has a high possibility of being converted to a permanent full-time position upon successful completion of the contract.

ASL Airlines Australia is excited to announce that our second 737-800BCF arrived in mid-July, enhancing our capacity to deliver freight across Auckland, Christchurch, Melbourne, and Sydney.

Apply now to be part of our expanding operations!

Who are we?

ASLA has over 20 years of Aviation experience and is an AOC of ASL Aviation Holdings. ASLA currently operates an all jet engine fleet, including the B737-800BCF and flexible passenger and cargo variants of the BAe146.  The ASLA team consists of 150 passionate and experienced employees who operate from our bases in Adelaide, Auckland, Brisbane, Cairns, Christchurch, Melbourne and Sydney.

ASL Aviation Holdings is a global aviation services holding company with a fleet of more than 160 aircraft, focused on cargo and passenger airline operations, aircraft leasing and maintenance. Headquartered in Dublin Ireland, the Group includes five wholly owned airlines; ASL Airlines Ireland, ASL Airlines Belgium, ASL Airlines France, ASL Airlines United Kingdom and most recently, ASL Airlines Australia. The Group also includes associate and joint venture airlines FlySafair in South Africa, K-Mile Asia in Thailand & QuikJet in India.

ASL’s airlines operate cargo networks for the world’s leading express parcel integrators and online retailers. Our group, joint-venture and associate airlines also operate scheduled and charter cargo and passenger services under ASL’s own airline brands and on behalf of airline ACMI customers and postal services. Globally, ASL has a team of 3,000 people of 51 different nationalities. The Group’s vision is to be the aviation service provider of choice through excellence, experience, and expertise.

Minimum qualifications & experience:

At least 5 years previous experience with an airline as a Technical Services Engineer.

Previous experience with the Boeing 737 fleet.

Familiarity with aviation regulations and compliance, including those issued by aviation authorities such as CASA.

Tasks & responsibilities:

The Technical Services Engineer reports to the CAM or delegate and is responsible for:

Evaluation of processes that improve system reliability in conjunction with the aircraft manufacturers, equipment manufacturers/suppliers, this is to include SB’s, AD’s, SL’s, and any other manufacturer/supplier documentation.

Development of processes and procedures as required for the technical operation of the aircraft fleet.

Assisting with defect analysis were required by communicating with the aircraft and equipment manufacturers/suppliers. Liaising with the maintenance suppliers to ensure that defects are rectified in the most efficient manner.

Maintaining a Library of information/history relevant to each aircraft's Modification Status and its systems.

Taking a lead role in major defect investigations.

Assist with Reliability monitoring, produce monthly Reliability Report (both computerised maintenance tracking system and Engine trends).

Updating the ASL Airlines Australia Reliability Manual so it reflects the ASL Airlines Australia reliability practices as they evolve.

Development of processes and procedures as required for ongoing refinement and tailoring of the computerised maintenance tracking system to the ASL Airlines Australia requirements.

Implement and manage all aspects related to aircraft EDTO configuration compliance with the applicable CMP documents and EDTO manuals.

Is responsible for ensuring EDTO standards and procedures are developed and maintained.

What are the benefits? 

Internal opportunities available within the ASL Group.

Onsite training, development, mentoring and career growth with the ability to relocate.

ID90 and access to exclusive discounts on travel/accommodation with our commercial partnerships.

Employee assistance program (EAP) available to all employees.

Commitment to a positive and inclusive work environment.

Engagement in DEI initiatives.

Opportunity to be part of a highly skilled and dedicated team.

Be part of a fast growing and rapidly expanding company.

If you would like to add value, make an impact and develop your skills, ASL is the company for you!

ASLA Values:

ASL Airlines Australia employees are lead with the ASL core values top of mind. Our values include Safety, People, Reliability, Quality, Profitability and Innovation. Our aim is to regard every customer as if they were our only customer, and to offer a service that is better than they could have expected. We know that diversity fosters greater innovation and better customer connection, that is why at ASL Airlines Australia we are committed to creating a diverse workforce, leveraging on each employee's unique skills and abilities providing a safe, secure and supportive, workplace.

We appreciate you taking the time to review our vacancy. For more information about ASL Airlines, please follow the link provided - https://aslairlines.com.au/

Ad Text:
Senior EDW Engineer - Federal Government

$125 + Super | Sydney or Melbourne | 12 Month Contract

We are partnering with a Federal Government Enterprise to engage Senior Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) Engineers to support a major data platform and analytics program.

This role is suited to experienced enterprise data warehouse specialists who enjoy working on large, governed data environments and owning delivery end-to-end.

**This is not a general analytics or BI role. Strong EDW experience is essential.

About the Role

You will join a central data warehouse stream and play a key role in:

Designing and enhancing enterprise data warehouse (EDW) solutions.
Building and maintaining core warehouse layers and integration logic.
Developing and optimising SQL and ETL / ELT processes.
Reviewing data models, setting development standards and supporting delivery quality.
Collaborating with business stakeholders to deliver consumable reporting and analytics data.
The environment is structured, enterprise-scale, and governed, ideal for engineers who value quality, performance and best practice.

Key Responsibilities

Design and implement EDW solutions across core and access layers.
Develop reusable ETL/ELT patterns.
Write, optimise, and tune SQL for large data sets.
Review and approve data designs and data models.

About You

You will have:

Demonstrable experience in enterprise data warehouse roles.
Strong hands-on experience with Snowflake, Teradata or similar EDW platforms.
Advanced SQL engineering and performance optimisation skills.
Experience with data modelling (3NF, dimensional, or hybrid approaches).
Exposure to DevOps and CI/CD practices (e.g. GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket).
Experience working in enterprise or regulated environments.
Australian citizenship is mandatory for this role.

Contract Details

Hours: 7.5 hours per day
Duration: 12 months
Location: Sydney or Melbourne
Working arrangement: Hybrid

What success looks like in this role:

We are seeking a highly experienced Microsoft 365 Consultant/Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will possess extensive experience in Microsoft 365 implementation, configuration, and migration projects. This role requires exceptional technical skills, strong communication abilities, and a solid understanding of both on-premises and cloud-based infrastructure.

Key Responsibilities

Work with Architect and execute Microsoft 365 implementation and migration projects, ensuring minimal disruption to business operations.

Implement comprehensive Microsoft 365 solutions tailored to client needs, encompassing various workloads including Exchange Online, SharePoint Online, OneDrive for Business, Teams, Teams Voice, Active Directory, and Entra ID.

Provide expert IT consulting services, guiding clients through the design and implementation phases of Microsoft 365 projects.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate Microsoft 365 solutions with existing on-premises infrastructure, such as Active Directory, servers, network, EUC, and applications.

Utilize PowerShell scripting to automate administrative tasks and enhance the efficiency of Microsoft 365 implementations.

Maintain up-to-date knowledge of Microsoft 365 technologies, industry trends, and best practices to ensure the delivery of cutting-edge solutions.

Identify and troubleshoot technical issues related to Microsoft 365 environments, providing timely resolutions to maintain optimal system performance.

Communicate effectively with clients, stakeholders, and team members to ensure the successful delivery of projects and fulfillment of client requirements.


Required Skills and Experience

Proven experience in delivering complex Microsoft 365 projects.

Expertise in Microsoft 365 implementation, configuration, and migration.

Strong technical skills across various Microsoft 365 workloads, including:

Exchange Online

SharePoint Online

OneDrive for Business

Teams

Teams Voice

Extensive knowledge of on-premises infrastructure, including Active Directory, servers, networks, EUC, and applications.

Proficiency in PowerShell scripting for automation and administrative tasks.

Excellent communication skills, with the ability to convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Strong troubleshooting skills and a methodical approach to problem-solving.

Ability to work independently and as part of a team, managing multiple priorities and deadlines.


You will be successful in this role if you have:

NV1 Security Clerance is required.

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.

Strong problem-solving and analytical abilities.

Familiarity with industry best practices and regulatory requirements related to Microsoft 365 and cloud-based solutions.

About Us

Crossmuller Systems Integration is a multi-disciplined engineering leader specialising in the design, build, and integration of advanced industrial systems across various customers and industries. Our project-based work spans diverse sectors including Food and Beverage, Data Centres, Manufacturing, Recycling, and Warehouse Automation.

The Role

We are seeking an experienced and motivated Systems Engineer to play a key role in the delivery of our projects. You will be responsible for the technical design, implementation, and commissioning of complex integration solutions. Your ability to understand the big picture while managing the technical details will be key to successfully interfacing with both our internal teams and our clients.

This role is ideal for a competent technical professional who excels in a project environment and is looking to grow their career, with a clear path towards technical leadership and mentorship opportunities.


Key Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and deploy integrated control systems, including PLC, SCADA, HMI, and industrial networking.

Architect and implement system solutions that meet client requirements, often involving integration with existing MES, ERP, and database applications.

Manage the technical aspects of projects, including system architecture design, specification writing, and code development.

Participation in commissioning activities, system troubleshooting, and providing client training.

Act as a technical point of contact for clients and collaborate effectively with other engineering departments to ensure seamless project execution.

Provide guidance and share knowledge with graduate engineers, contributing to the team's collective expertise.

 

About You

You are an experienced engineer with a proven track record in systems integration within industrial environments.

You thrive in a project-based role where no two days are the same, and you enjoy the challenge of adapting to different technical requirements and scopes.

You are a confident problem-solver who can work autonomously to lead commissioning activities and interact directly with clients.

You have a strong understanding of how different systems (electrical, mechanical, IT) interact and are skilled at making them work together.

You possess strong communication and collaboration skills, and the ability to guide others is looked upon favourably as a key to future growth within our team.

 

Career Growth

At Crossmuller, we are committed to the professional development of our staff. For the right candidate, this role offers a clear pathway for advancement. We value and will support your growth into technical leadership and mentorship positions, where you can take on greater responsibility for project deliverables and guide the next generation of engineers.

 

Essential Skills and Experience:

3+ years of experience in a similar systems integration, automation, or controls role.

Proven proficiency with industrial control platforms (e.g., Siemens TIA Portal, Rockwell Studio 5000/ControlLogix, Schneider EcoStruxure).

Strong experience with SCADA/HMI systems (e.g., Inductive Automation Ignition, Aveva System Platform, Aveva Citect/Plant SCADA, Siemens WinCC, Rockwell FactoryTalk View).

Solid understanding of industrial networking (switches, routers, VLANs, firewall configurations) and communication protocols (Modbus. BACnet, OPC UA, MQTT).

Experience in database integration (SQL) and higher-level programming languages (e.g., C#, Python) is highly regarded.

Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to produce clear technical documentation.

Eligibility Requirements:

A degree in Software, Mechatronic, Electrical, or a related engineering field.

Available to work full-time and willing to travel to client sites for commissioning as required.

Possess a valid driver's licence.

Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency.

About the role

Join DataIQ as we expand our Data & AI practice to build modern data products on Microsoft Fabric. You'll be part of the team that owns ingestion, orchestration and transformation Microsoft Fabric, Spark and Power BI, delivering a variety of services to our clients that power enterprise semantic models and reports.

Australian work rights are required for this position.

What you'll do

Build and manage the Microsoft Fabric platform for client engagements, including governance, capacity planning, and performance optimisation.

Build and Oversee the Reporting function, ensuring timely delivery of semantic models and Power BI reports aligned with business needs.

Ingest and transform data using Fabric Data Factory, pipelines, and Spark notebooks (PySpark).

Model curated Delta tables and medallion layers optimized for Direct Lake and semantic models.

Automate reliability: parameterized pipelines, scheduling, monitoring, alerting; build runbooks for recovery.

Tune performance and cost (partitioning strategies, incremental refresh, capacity awareness).

Collaborate with stakeholders to align data products with strategic goals and reporting requirements.

What you'll bring

Hands-on experience with Microsoft Fabric (Data Factory, Synapse Data Engineering) and Spark/PySpark, with a minimum of 5 years' experience with Data Factory.

A minimum of 2 years hands-on Microsoft Fabric experience is required.

Strong SQL and Delta Lake experience; medallion architecture patterns.

Deep knowledge of OneLake, Data Factory in Fabric, Synapse Data Engineering/Spark, Real-Time Analytics, and Power BI (Service, Desktop).

Experience managing enterprise reporting functions and aligning data models with business KPIs.

CI/CD and deployment pipelines knowledge; Git familiarity.

Nice to have: KQL, streaming/Eventstreams, Databricks/Azure background, Purview lineage.

Certification preferred: Fabric Data Engineer Associate and PL-300 familiarity.

How to apply

Apply with your CV and a short cover letter highlighting recent Fabric/Spark projects. Portfolio or Git links welcome.

Job Title: Software Engineer Manager (MERN stack, AWS DevOps)
Ad Text:
The Role

As Software Development Manager, you will provide technical leadership, delivery ownership, and people leadership for our development teams. You will ensure we deliver high-quality, scalable SaaS solutions predictably, while continuously improving our Agile maturity and engineering practices.

You’ll work closely with Product and senior stakeholders to align technical decisions with commercial outcomes, while fostering a culture of wellbeing, growth, and accountability.




What You'll Be Doing

Lead and mentor software engineers, providing hands-on technical guidance and coaching

Own Agile delivery: sprint planning, execution, retrospectives, and continuous improvement

Ensure delivery of secure, scalable SaaS solutions aligned to customer and business needs

Review designs and solutions to maintain high standards of quality, security, performance, and resilience

Identify risks, bottlenecks, and technical debt early and act decisively

Drive improvements in engineering practices, tooling, and delivery cadence

Partner with Product and stakeholders to translate strategy into executable delivery

Support career development, performance growth, and succession planning within the team

Foster a high-performance culture grounded in trust, wellbeing, and accountability




What We Are Looking For (Must-Have)

Proven experience leading teams in a Commercial SaaS environment (this is essential)

Strong background as a software engineer who has progressed into leadership

Hands-on experience with Agile development (Scrum/Kanban) and sprint-based delivery

Demonstrated success delivering commercial, customer-facing software products

Deep technical credibility, able to challenge designs, guide architecture, and assess trade-offs

Experience coaching engineers across varying levels of seniority

Strong communication skills, able to align technical teams with business priorities

Strong AWS experience with a clear focus on cost-conscious engineering and cloud cost optimisation and modern DevOps practices




Nice to Have

Experience in FinTech, RegTech, or other regulated environments

Interest in emerging technologies such as AI/LLMs in SaaS products

Experience applying SRE principles to improve reliability, availability, incident response, and production stability in SaaS systems




What Success Looks Like

Predictable, high-quality delivery with fewer late-stage surprises

Engaged engineers who feel supported, challenged, and clear on their growth paths

Continuous improvement in Agile maturity and engineering practices

Early identification and resolution of technical and delivery risks




Welcome to MVSI!

We are a dynamic team of 70+ professionals, spread across the Globe with offices in Australia, EMEA, the US and the Philippines. Our innovative SaaS product is trusted by banks, Fintech’s, and crypto services worldwide to manage their AML/KYC Compliance requirements. We have always harnessed the power of cutting-edge technology and are expanding the exciting realm of LLM (think ChatGPT) to further elevate our offerings. Our company culture is built on a foundation of support and commitment to career development.

We truly value our people and invite you to join us to experience all that we have to offer!

This role is ideal for a hands-on technical leader who has grown from software engineering into people leadership and thrives in modern SaaS, Agile environments.




Why Join MVSI?

Get an awesome career! Ours is a specialised industry, and experience is in short supply.

Global impact – Your work directly supports financial crime prevention worldwide

True SaaS scale – Build and evolve a commercial, multi-partner platform

Modern engineering culture – Agile, continuous improvement, pragmatic delivery

We are the leading online platform for comparing and buying business insurance. 

Not to toot our own horn, but we’re shaking things up in the SME business insurance market! We’re all about making it easy and efficient for small businesses to get the perfect coverage they need to stay protected. Say goodbye to headaches and hello to hassle-free insurance!

The purpose of this role is to contribute to changing how BizCover operates using data to drive decisions and exceed our strategic growth objectives.

Responsibilities:

Implement reusable patterns and model structures in MSSQL, dbt Cloud, and Snowflake 
Monitor data quality, lineage, and job health

Requirements


Ideally would have 4-6 years of experience.
Technical experience with Snowflake, Fivetran, dbt Cloud, MSSQL

Strong documentation and technical communication skills
Hands-on experience using AI-assisted development tools (e.g., SQL/dbt copilots, LLMs for documentation, testing, or refactoring) to improve productivity and code quality.

Benefits

Quarterly recognition awards

Employee benefits package

About Us

Crossmuller Systems Integration is a multi-disciplined engineering leader specialising in the design, build, and integration of advanced industrial systems across various customers and industries. Our project-based work spans diverse sectors including Food and Beverage, Data Centres, Manufacturing, Recycling, and Warehouse Automation.

The Role

We are seeking an experienced and motivated Systems Engineer to play a key role in the delivery of our projects. You will be responsible for the technical design, implementation, and commissioning of complex integration solutions. Your ability to understand the big picture while managing the technical details will be key to successfully interfacing with both our internal teams and our clients.

This role is ideal for a competent technical professional who excels in a project environment and is looking to grow their career, with a clear path towards technical leadership and mentorship opportunities.


Key Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and deploy integrated control systems, including PLC, SCADA, HMI, and industrial networking.

Architect and implement system solutions that meet client requirements, often involving integration with existing MES, ERP, and database applications.

Manage the technical aspects of projects, including system architecture design, specification writing, and code development.

Participation in commissioning activities, system troubleshooting, and providing client training.

Act as a technical point of contact for clients and collaborate effectively with other engineering departments to ensure seamless project execution.

Provide guidance and share knowledge with graduate engineers, contributing to the team's collective expertise.

 

About You

You are an experienced engineer with a proven track record in systems integration within industrial environments.

You thrive in a project-based role where no two days are the same, and you enjoy the challenge of adapting to different technical requirements and scopes.

You are a confident problem-solver who can work autonomously to lead commissioning activities and interact directly with clients.

You have a strong understanding of how different systems (electrical, mechanical, IT) interact and are skilled at making them work together.

You possess strong communication and collaboration skills, and the ability to guide others is looked upon favourably as a key to future growth within our team.

 

Career Growth

At Crossmuller, we are committed to the professional development of our staff. For the right candidate, this role offers a clear pathway for advancement. We value and will support your growth into technical leadership and mentorship positions, where you can take on greater responsibility for project deliverables and guide the next generation of engineers.

 

Essential Skills and Experience:

3+ years of experience in a similar systems integration, automation, or controls role.

Proven proficiency with industrial control platforms (e.g., Siemens TIA Portal, Rockwell Studio 5000/ControlLogix, Schneider EcoStruxure).

Strong experience with SCADA/HMI systems (e.g., Inductive Automation Ignition, Aveva System Platform, Aveva Citect/Plant SCADA, Siemens WinCC, Rockwell FactoryTalk View).

Solid understanding of industrial networking (switches, routers, VLANs, firewall configurations) and communication protocols (Modbus. BACnet, OPC UA, MQTT).

Experience in database integration (SQL) and higher-level programming languages (e.g., C#, Python) is highly regarded.

Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to produce clear technical documentation.

Eligibility Requirements:

A degree in Software, Mechatronic, Electrical, or a related engineering field.

Available to work full-time and willing to travel to client sites for commissioning as required.

Possess a valid driver's licence.

Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency.

Working alongside Senior ML Engineers, Data Scientists and Clinical stakeholders, you'll contribute across the full ML lifecycle, from model development through to production deployment in a highly regulated healthcare environment.

What You'll Be Doing


Develop, train and evaluate machine learning models
Deploy models into scalable, production-grade services
Contribute to batch and/or streaming ML systems
Integrate ML services with enterprise and clinical platforms via APIs
Implement monitoring, logging, testing and alerting

Collaborate in Agile teams with Data, Engineering, Product and Clinical partners

What We're Looking For


2-3+ years' experience in software engineering with applied machine learning

Experience with batch or streaming ML systems

I-MED Radiology Network is Australia and New Zealand's largest diagnostic imaging network, offering medical imaging and radiology services including x-ray, PET, CT, MRI, Nuclear Medicine, Ultrasound, Mammography and interventional procedures.

At I-MED Radiology Network there is a strong belief that we can be the most respected and trusted medical imaging specialists in the world. That's our vision, underpinned by our purpose - to help save lives and reduce uncertainty. We strive to be the provider of choice, providing answers to health questions and delivering high quality care and service to our patients and referrers, every time.

Why I-MED?

Hybrid working and flexible locations

Purpose-driven, collaborative culture

This is a great opportunity to grow your ML engineering career while delivering AI solutions that make a meaningful difference in healthcare.
